Usage: specifyCellPad [-help] <leaf_cellName> {<padding> | [[-right <padding>] [-left <padding>] [-top <padding>] [-bottom <padding>]]}

-help                      # Prints out the command usage
<leaf_cellName>            # specify leaf cells to which to add padding
                           # (string, required)
<padding>                  # specify a factor to calculate the padding
                           # dimension on the right side (int, required)
-bottom <padding>          # specify a factor to calculate the padding
                           # dimension on the bottom side
                           # (int, optional, min=0, max=500)
-left <padding>            # specify a factor to calculate the padding
                           # dimension on the left side
                           # (int, optional, min=0, max=1000)
-right <padding>           # specify a factor to calculate the padding
                           # dimension on the right side
                           # (int, optional, min=0, max=1000)
-top <padding>             # specify a factor to calculate the padding
                           # dimension on the top side
                           # (int, optional, min=0, max=500)